entries.meaning: A fancy twisting or curling shape usually made from a series of spirals and loops.

verbs.description: curlicue (third-person singular simple present curlicues, present participle curlicuing, simple past and past participle curlicued)

entries.meaning: (transitive and intransitive) To make or adorn (something) with curlicues, or as if with curlicues.
